     ). The results completely confirmed the yeast two-hybrid data. Thus, the full-length α-actinin did not bind; neither did N-terminal deletion constructs with either the isoform-specific first 18 residues or the first CH domain deleted. The R1-C construct did bind but N-terminal extension of R1 by 15 residues inhibited Z-repeat binding.
    </p>
